         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">Melbourne ¶ 11/9/78. ¶  ¶ I was pleasingly surprised, dear Mr Day, ¶  to receive your kind letter this morning. ¶  It was very kind of you, to think of me and my wishes of plants during your travels a...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">78.09.11a</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">To [George] Day</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="en">RB MSSS M114, Library, Royal Botanic Gardens Melbourne.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <note xml:id="ftn1" type="footnote" n="1">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.1665in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.1665in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">MS found with a specimen of <seg style="font-style: italic; ">Donatia novae-zelandiae</seg> (MEL 2469031), folded to make an envelope in which to store the specimen and inscribed on the verso: ‘Donatia Novae Zeelandia | Otago mountains | 1878 | Petrie’.</p>
               </note>Melbourne</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">11/9/78.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I was pleasingly surprised, dear Mr Day,<note xml:id="ftn2" type="footnote" n="2">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.1665in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.1665in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">Not identified. However, M is known to have been corresponding with George Porter Day at this period, and Day was sending him specimens; see G. Day to M, 25 January 1879, and G. Day to M, 6 March 1879.</p>
               </note> to receive your kind letter this morning.<note xml:id="ftn3" type="footnote" n="3">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.1665in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.1665in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">Letter not found.</p>
               </note> It was very kind of you, to think of me and my wishes of plants during your travels and business engagements.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>The so called native orange-tree is <name key="Capparis%20Mitchelli">Capparis Mitchelli</name>
               <note xml:id="ftn4" type="footnote" n="4">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.1665in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.1665in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">Capparis mitchellii?</p>
               </note> of Professor Lindley.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Any collections of yours will be very valuable for my supplemental volumes of the Australian Flora.<note xml:id="ftn5" type="footnote" n="5">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.1665in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.1665in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">Text finishes part-way down the sheet, without valediction; it thus appears that the letter was neither finished nor sent.</p>
               </note>
            </p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="plant%20names" xml:lang="en">
               <name key="Capparis%20Mitchelli">Capparis Mitchelli</name>
            </p>
         </div>
      </body>
